OMG when I was in Cabo San Lucas the cockroachs were the size of rats! and there were several spider/bug things I have no idea what they were. I made sure I checked between the sheets before I crawled into bed everynight.

  Kay


Ron Lederer &lt;ronriko@...&gt; wrote:
                  Ah, a subject I can comment on with authority... killing ants and things that sting is my specialty here in Mexico...you&#39;ll love the simple answer...laundry detergent.  I can tell you stories of tiny crazy ants to ants as large as half your thumb...tried all kinds of things like chlorine...acid...but a hand full of cheap, cheap, blue laundry detergent mixed in water will kill ants on the spot...dead, done, gone, ready for an EVP session.  What a blessing since I am highly allergic to all pesticides.  Getting ants out of an electrical system is another matter.  I have them running along by house electrical lines and must wait for them to show their face before I soap em.    Ron L


